From 0f60da8a3118cd0a4e6e123a14694f7c93d8b6dd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Juan Manuel Lopez Carrillo <juanmanuellopezcarrillo@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 04:32:33 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 102/106] thermal: sun8i: a523: no fabricar 183C si el canal
 NPU aun no tiene dato

La zona de GPU del A523 lee el sensor NPU en lugar del GPU (receta del
vendor: el canal GPU es poco fiable). Pero la guarda 'ths have no data
yet' de sun8i_ths_get_temp solo valida el registro del canal GPU: si el
del NPU todavia esta a 0 (primera conversion pendiente justo tras
habilitar el bloque), la formula de dos tramos convierte raw 0 en
~183.6C y el trip critico de 110C apaga la placa (visto en campo:
'gpu-thermal: critical temperature reached' + poweroff a los 2.8s de
arrancar, con la placa a ~50C reales).

Si el registro del NPU esta a 0, conservar la muestra del propio canal
GPU (ya validada no-cero por el caller) hasta que el NPU tenga dato.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 drivers/thermal/sun8i_thermal.c | 18 ++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/thermal/sun8i_thermal.c b/drivers/thermal/sun8i_thermal.c
index 8774ef8d6..51f0cb338 100644
--- a/drivers/thermal/sun8i_thermal.c
+++ b/drivers/thermal/sun8i_thermal.c
@@ -139,10 +139,24 @@ static int sun55i_a523_calc_temp(struct ths_device *tmdev, int id, int reg)
 	/*
 	 * The GPU sensor (id 2) is unreliable on this silicon; the vendor
 	 * driver reads the NPU sensor (id 3) in its place, so do the same.
+	 *
+	 * Right after the block is enabled the NPU channel may not have
+	 * completed its first conversion yet, leaving its data register at
+	 * zero. The caller's "no data yet" check only covers the GPU
+	 * channel's own register, and raw 0 computes to a bogus ~183C,
+	 * which trips the 110C critical shutdown (seen in the field as a
+	 * poweroff 2.8s into boot). Keep the GPU channel's own sample,
+	 * already validated non-zero by the caller, until the NPU channel
+	 * has data.
 	 */
-	if (id == 2)
+	if (id == 2) {
+		int npu = 0;
+
 		regmap_read(tmdev->regmap,
-			    tmdev->chip->temp_data_base + 0x4 * 3, &reg);
+			    tmdev->chip->temp_data_base + 0x4 * 3, &npu);
+		if (npu)
+			reg = npu;
+	}
 
 	return sun55i_a523_calc_temp_raw(reg);
 }
